Title: Infrared Regularization of Yang-Mills Theories
Authors: Alberto Blasi and Nicola Maggiore
Comments: final version to appear in Mod.Phys.Lett.A. 8 pages + cover,
  plain LaTeX
Report-no: UGVA-DPT-96-03-236
Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A11 (1996) 1665-1674
\\
  We introduce an infrared regulator in Yang--Mills theories under the form of
a mass term for the nonabelian fields. We show that the resulting action, built
in a covariant linear gauge, is multiplicatively renormalizable by proving the
validity at all orders of the Slavnov identity defining the theory.
